{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-718-Introducing-Core-NFC"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc17\/718","isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (11 min)"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Currently iPhone supports only "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reading"}]},{"type":"text","text":" NFC, they can’t write to NFC tags (this changed from iOS 13, any iPhone from 7 and later can write)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To use Core NFC capabilities we need to:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"enable its entitlement.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"add a usage description in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"info.plist","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to read:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"The app has to start a “tag reading session”, which will be valid as long as the app stays in the foreground with the NFC UI visible (see below). Each session has a 60 seconds lifespan, after which a new session has to be started."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two modes:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Single Tag: the session aims to read one tag and will end as soon as any tag is read."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multiple Tags Session: the session will continue even after reading one or more tags (up to 60s).","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NFC UI:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC17-718-ui","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Written-By","type":"heading","text":"Written By","level":2},{"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"https:\/\/avatars.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5277837?v=4"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"text":"Federico Zanetello","anchor":"Federico-Zanetello","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"zntfdr.dev","isActive":true}]}]}],"numberOfColumns":5,"type":"row"},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","level":2},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal Notice"}]}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2024 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-718-introducing-core-nfc"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Core NFC is an exciting new framework that enables you to read NFC tags in your apps on iPhone 7 and iPhone 7 Plus.  Learn how to integrate Core NFC into your apps, key requirements for using this feature, and start thinking about the new kinds of apps that are enabled with NFC capabilities.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC17","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Introducing Core NFC","role":"sampleCode"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","title":"WWDC17","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.13, tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"Core NFC","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","abstract":[{"text":"Software engineer with a strong passion for well-written code, thought-out composable architectures, automation, tests, and more.","type":"text"}],"title":"Federico Zanetello (214 notes)","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr"},"WWDC17-718-ui":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC17-718-ui.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-718-ui"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc17/718":{"checksum":null,"u